The paper deals with the problem of estimating the weight of a maximum weighted matching in a graph, which is a problem in graph algorithms and optimization. The paper also discusses the use of this problem in estimating weights of planar graphs and bounded-arboricity graphs, which are topics in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also involves the use of approximation algorithms and information theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
